    "(3) The temperature α is a hyperparameter.",
    "L is the vanilla NLL (see Fig. 9 for an example), and the weights w are the softmax output of the L/α.",
    "Theoretically, we prove that optimizing towards the proposed weighted loss achieves a convergence rate with O(1/ √ T) with T representing the update iterations, see App.",
    "K for detailed proofs.",
    "The rate of convergence is the same as optimizing towards the standard NLL version."
